The `getCookie()` function in JavaScript allows you to retrieve the value of a specific cookie based on its key. Here is an example implementation of the `getCookie()` function:

``` javascript
function getCookie(key) {
  // Split document.cookie into an array of individual cookies
  var cookies = document.cookie.split(";");

  // Loop through each cookie in the array
  for(var i = 0; i < cookies.length; i++) {
    // Split the current cookie into its key and value
    var cookie = cookies[i].trim().split("=");

    // Compare the key to the specified key
    if(cookie[0] === key) {
      // Return the value if the keys match
      return cookie[1];
    }
  }

  // Return null if the cookie was not found
  return null;
}
```

Using this function, you can retrieve the value of a cookie by passing the cookie key as a parameter. For example:

``` javascript
var username = getCookie("username");
```

This will retrieve the value of a cookie with the key "username" and store it in the `username` variable. Note that the `getCookie()` function will return `null` if the specified cookie cannot be found.

